	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Septr 5615</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I had intended&#44; my dear sir&#44;<lb/> to request you to copy form the <sic>asmonean</sic><lb/> then to the Occident&#44; the advertisement<lb/> of my translation of <persName>Templo&#39;s</persName> Hebrew Grammar<lb/> when it occurred to me that you might<lb/> not feel indisposed to join yourself<lb/> in an attempt to supply good school<lb/> books much wanted.  I stop&#44; therefore<lb/> for the present my publication&#44; to make<lb/> to you the following suggestion or<lb/> offer&#44; as you may feel disposed to<lb/> regard it.</p>
				<p>We will jointly publish <persName>L. L D&#39;s</persName><lb/> Series of School Books to consist<lb/> of a Hebrew Grammar&#44; a reading Book&#44;<lb/> History of the Jews&#44; <add>&#63;</add> Introduction to the<lb/> scriptures and some others&#59; The facilities<lb/> you possess for publishing there I</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>must of course confess renders your<lb/> alliance a very desirable one.  I on<lb/> my part can offer you all literary<lb/> labor required by you one half <sic>expences</sic><lb/> and if you prefer it assist in preparing<lb/> for press&#44; besides using my best exertions<lb/> and enlisting those of some few friends<lb/> I have in <placeName>England</placeName> &#38; <placeName>America</placeName> for the<lb/> adoption &#38; circulation of the books.<lb/>  Should you think well of the undertaking<lb/> may I hope to hear soon from you.  Your<lb/> views on the subject will in any<lb/> case be acceptable.  I think it right<lb/> to inform you at once that in <hi rend="underline">no other</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">quarter at all</hi> have I even hinted<lb/> a desire for combining in such an undertaking.<lb/>  I think the attempt might be made<lb/> by any two competent persons to the<lb/> extent say of 1000 dollars each with<lb/> perfect safety.  Subscribers before hand<lb/> can scarcely be hoped for&#44; though it<lb/> would seem a &#8220;Holy Alliance&#8221; for the</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>similar purpose had been made in<lb/> other quarters.</p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
				<p>I only sold 2 more <sic>setts</sic><lb/> of the Prayers in consequence<lb/> of their coming so late&#8212;with the<lb/> Occidents I believe which we<lb/> never got till <hi rend="underline">the latter end of the month</hi><lb/> I have yet had no receipts for you<lb/> but will hand them to <persName>Mr Joseph</persName> as soon<lb/> as <sic>realised</sic>.</p>
		</body>
